Chima Azubuike, Gombe The Senator representing Gombe Central and Chairman Senate Committee on Maritime, Danjuma Goje, on Sunday, said he would not contest elections again. He, however, said he would remain in politics. Goje spoke at the venue of his empowerment outreach at the Pantami Stadium. He said he was grateful to God for his position as a senator, after successful terms as a state governor, commissioner and minister. He said, “I will be involved in all political activities but will not contest for any elective position in the future. I’m grateful to God. READ ALSO: Nine ex-govs whose corruption cases are forgotten “114 wards will get one motorcycle each with 50,000. Each of the eleven LGAs will get a vehicle, while five executives in the LGAs will get tricycle each.” Copyright PUNCH.
